The [[Liaoshi]] records in Chapter 53:

{{quote| <U+570B><U+8A9E><U+8B02><U+662F><U+65E5><U+70BA><U+300C><U+8A0E><U+8CFD><U+54BF><U+5152><U+300D><U+3002><U+300C><U+8A0E><U+300D><U+4E94><U+FF1B><U+300C><U+8CFD><U+54BF><U+5152><U+300D><U+FF0C><U+6708><U+4E5F><U+3002>}} 

{{quote| In the national (Khitan) language this day (5th day of the 5th lunar month) is called 'Tao Saiyier'. 'Tao' means five; 'Saiyier' means moon.}} 

'Tao Saiyier' corresponds to Mongolian 'tavan sar' (fifth moon/month). The Turkic equivalent would be 'beshinchi ay' while the Tungusic equivalent would be 'sunja biya'.

